    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** (86.40) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (80.43) leading the charge. **Yordan Alvarez** is our premier play, bolstered by a massive +16% park factor and an elite xwOBA of .393, making him the centerpiece of the offense against Baz. Meanwhile, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** earns an elite grade despite the lower batting order slot; his +19% SP skill boost and the extreme threat he poses on the basepaths against a pitcher with a slow delivery make him a high-upside play for our crucial stolen base category. **Kyle Schwarber** (78.40) and **Trea Turner** (74.91) also provide significant firepower against Mahle, with **Kyle Schwarber** benefiting from a strong historical BvP edge and **Trea Turner** providing the speed-first spark at the top of the lineup.\n\nOur optimization process was most difficult regarding the bench, where **Caleb Durbin** (49.05) and **Carson Benge** (49.75) occupied the bottom of the active lineup. While **Caleb Durbin** is a priority for his stolen base potential, his move to the #9 spot significantly dampened his efficiency score, nearly pushing him out of the starting rotation. We continue to monitor the status of **Christian Yelich** and **Lars Nootbaar**, both of whom remain sidelined on the IL, leaving our active roster thin on depth. While **Colt Keith** and **Zac Veen** were considered, neither are available for active duty today, forcing us to lean heavily on the current core to maximize our 5x5 production.\n\nWe must remain cautious of the matchup against high-skill arms today. While **Dillon Dingler** (63.75) looks solid against P\u00e9rez, the overall team efficiency is susceptible to the risk associated with facing pitchers like Ryan, who carries a 3.32 xERA against **Luke Raley**. We are prioritizing stolen base opportunities through **Pete Crow-Armstrong** and **Trea Turner** to maintain our edge in the league\u2019s scarcest category, even in games where the raw run-production projections are tempered by the opposing starter\u2019s skill. Our bench remains locked with **Chase Meidroth**, **Gary Sanchez**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, **Pedro Ramirez**, and **Luis Pena** waiting for a favorable platoon shift or injury update.",
